{"info": {"author": "Jaeman An", "author_email": "ajmbell@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# pytest-board -- Continuous pytest runner with awesome visualization\n\n**pytest-board** is a testing visualization tool for pytest runner. Works with `ptb`. Use it instead of `py.test`. \n\n![](https://github.com/kuss/pytest-board/raw/master/docs/pytest_board_screenshot.png)\n\n## Installation\n\n\t$ pip install pytest-board\n\n## Usage\n\nYou can just use instead of pytest runner.\n\n\t$ ptb\n\nWatch the test results display in your browser at:\n\n\thttp://localhost:8080\n\n## Motivation\n\nThis project is inspired by [GoConvey](https://github.com/smartystreets/goconvey). Some code are from other libraries:\n\n- [GoConvey](https://github.com/smartystreets/goconvey)\n- [pytest-watch](https://github.com/joeyespo/pytest-watch)\n- [pytest-json-report](https://github.com/numirias/pytest-json-report)\n\n## License\n\nThis software is licensed under the [MIT license](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License).\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "http://github.com/kuss/pytest-board", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "pytest-board", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-board/", "platform": "any", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-board/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "http://github.com/kuss/pytest-board"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pytest-board/0.1.0/", "requires_dist": ["pytest-watch (==4.2.0)"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Local continuous test runner with pytest and watchdog.", "version": "0.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p># pytest-board \u2013 Continuous pytest runner with awesome visualization</p>\n<p><strong>pytest-board</strong> is a testing visualization tool for pytest runner. Works with <cite>ptb</cite>. Use it instead of <cite>py.test</cite>.</p>\n<p>![](<a href=\"https://github.com/kuss/pytest-board/raw/master/docs/pytest_board_screenshot.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/kuss/pytest-board/raw/master/docs/pytest_board_screenshot.png</a>)</p>\n<p>## Installation</p>\n<blockquote>\n$ pip install pytest-board</blockquote>\n<p>## Usage</p>\n<p>You can just use instead of pytest runner.</p>\n<blockquote>\n$ ptb</blockquote>\n<p>Watch the test results display in your browser at:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<a href=\"http://localhost:8080\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://localhost:8080</a></blockquote>\n<p>## Motivation</p>\n<p>This project is inspired by [GoConvey](<a href=\"https://github.com/smartystreets/goconvey\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/smartystreets/goconvey</a>). Some code are from other libraries:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>[GoConvey](<a href=\"https://github.com/smartystreets/goconvey\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/smartystreets/goconvey</a>)</li>\n<li>[pytest-watch](<a href=\"https://github.com/joeyespo/pytest-watch\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/joeyespo/pytest-watch</a>)</li>\n<li>[pytest-json-report](<a href=\"https://github.com/numirias/pytest-json-report\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/numirias/pytest-json-report</a>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>## License</p>\n<p>This software is licensed under the [MIT license](<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_License</a>).</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 4718263, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "063539cce246077c4c632f563663d2fa", "sha256": "0ad68df530b52b577fb40854626a07c290d2a200ac4552cbee08791751cdeacf"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pytest_board-0.1.0-py3.7.egg", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "063539cce246077c4c632f563663d2fa", "packagetype": "bdist_egg", "python_version": "3.7", "requires_python": null, "size": 1439286, "upload_time": "2019-01-20T13:15:50